verses.roman:
mahānubhavera ei sahaja 'svabhāva' haya
āpanāra guṇa nāhi āpane kahaya"

synonyms: mahānubhavera—of those who are advanced in realization; ei—this; sahaja—natural; svabhāva—characteristic; haya—is; āpanāra guṇa—their own personal qualities; nāhi—do not; āpane—personally; kahaya—speak.
translation: "This is a natural characteristic of those advanced in devotional service. They do not personally speak of their own good qualities."
